From: Vincenzo <vincenzo@example.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Jun 2026 14:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] pidfd-utils: include <sys/pidfd.h> when available

On glibc 2.36+, pidfd_open() and pidfd_send_signal() are declared in
<sys/pidfd.h>, not in <sys/types.h>.  Without including this header,
the compiler sees implicit declarations when HAVE_PIDFD_OPEN and
HAVE_PIDFD_SEND_SIGNAL are defined (meaning configure found the
functions in libc), but the declarations are not visible.

Fix by adding #include <sys/pidfd.h> inside the #if block where
UL_HAVE_PIDFD is defined, guarded by __has_include for portability.

Signed-off-by: Vincenzo <vincenzo@example.com>

diff --git a/include/pidfd-utils.h b/include/pidfd-utils.h
index e1f1af0..1a2b3c4 100644
--- a/include/pidfd-utils.h
+++ b/include/pidfd-utils.h
@@ -5,6 +5,10 @@
 # include <sys/syscall.h>
 # if defined(SYS_pidfd_send_signal) && defined(SYS_pidfd_open)
 #  include <sys/types.h>
+#  ifdef __has_include
+#   if __has_include(<sys/pidfd.h>)
+#    include <sys/pidfd.h>
+#   endif
+#  endif
 
 #  ifndef HAVE_PIDFD_SEND_SIGNAL
 static inline int pidfd_send_signal(int pidfd, int sig, siginfo_t *info,
